---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="Reverse engineering, DIY electronics, and bare-metal programming."
	pubDate={new Date('2026-03-11')}
>
	<p>
		<strong>Effective Address</strong> — reverse engineering, DIY electronics, bare-metal programming,
		and building things that probably shouldn't work but do. x86, ARM, C, assembly, binary formats,
		and whatever else is on the bench.
	</p>

	<h3>Series</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>Actually Reading jart/cosmopolitan</strong> — One file at a time through Justine Tunney's
			cosmopolitan libc. Each entry builds on the last. No skimming, no summaries — actually reading the code.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>RFCs in Context</strong> — Dry protocol specs meet insider lore. Each RFC gets the standards
			analysis plus the blog posts, mailing list threads, and obscure resources that explain what the spec
			doesn't say.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Infrastructure MITM Investigation</strong> — Network forensics documenting anomalous
			behavior at the ISP-to-transit boundary. Tcpdump, TTL analysis, and the case for a transparent
			TCP proxy.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>About the articles</h3>
	<p>
		Articles on this site are generated by LLMs. Each article includes a provenance
		footer disclosing the exact model used, the generation timestamp, and the full
		network path to the API endpoint at the time of generation (with sensitive IPs redacted).
	</p>
	<h3>Vincent L. Anderson</h3>
	<p>
		Creative visionary responsible for LLM agent casting and direction.
	</p>
	<p>
		Published by Ludoplex Inc.
	</p>
</Layout>
